Antarctica has seen a whole bunch of harsh years recently, and it doesn‚Äôt look like things are going to improve anytime soon.

Source: http://arctic.atmos.uiuc.edu/jpg.
Of course the extra sea ice we‚Äôve been seeing at the South Pole doesn‚Äôt mean these dignified birds¬†will become extinct any time soon. Like polar bears, they‚Äôve survived far worse conditions. But¬†it does mean the weaker ones aren‚Äôt going to fare as well and some will have to make an agonizing, early departure from Earth.
Already I‚Äôm¬†seeing emperor¬†penguins falling from the sky to their death! Must be those damn man-made aerosols cooling the southern hemisphere.
