Share this...FacebookTwitterFOX NEWS here reports on the decommissioning of a NASA satellite which has provided lots of data for the climate change discussion over 11 and half years.

Jason-1 satellite. Photo: NASA
It has circled¬†the globe more than¬† 53,500 times. FOX writes that ‚Äúthe joint U.S. and French satellite was decommissioned this week after its last remaining transmitter failed, according to a NASA statement‚Äú.
The satellite scanned the ocean surface and mapped sea level for more than 95 percent of the planet‚Äôs ice-free¬†ocean area. According to Jason-1‚Äôs readings, it has detected a rise of nearly 1.6 inches over the last 20 years. Its radar¬†altimeter determined sea levels¬†to within a few centimeters.


